<font color="#FF0000">THE MONUMENT</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 28 23:19:41 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Each time I go to the Vietnam Veterans Memorial in Washington <br>
D.C. I cry. I cry for all those lives lost for nothing. I cry for all the
<br>
families who lost a son or daughter on both sides for nothing. I cry <br>
for all those thousands of human beings. What was so important? A <br>
lot of money for big business. Who were they?..... They were the <br>
people who worked there. They were the  ones who gave silent <br>
consent to the war and its needless deaths. Why didn't they ask <br>
questions?....................Why didn't anyone ask?<br><br>

